.TH QT-CALCULATOR-GUI 1 "March 2025" "qt-stdio-calculator" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
qt-calculator-gui \- Qt-based calculator using stdio backends

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qt-calculator-gui
[\fB--PHP\fR] [\fB--BASH\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
qt-calculator-gui is a Qt Widgets calculator that communicates with a backend
over standard input/output. Backends are installed in:

/usr/local/libexec/qt-stdio-calculator/

The GUI shows a two-line display:

Line 1: current numeric value
.br
Line 2: current operator (C, +, -, *, ÷, =)

The division operator is displayed as "÷" while the backend still uses "/".

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --PHP
Use Calculator.php (default).
.TP
.B --BASH
Use Calculator.sh.

.SH FILES
/usr/local/bin/qt-calculator-gui
.br
/usr/local/libexec/qt-stdio-calculator/Calculator.php
.br
/usr/local/libexec/qt-stdio-calculator/Calculator.sh
.br
/usr/share/applications/qt-calculator-gui.desktop

